====Node M Land-Based Aircraft Proficiency Leveling====
*If you wish to rank up your [[Aircraft Proficiency]] , you may utilize node M to do so.
*'''Your Land-Base' Range must be 8 or higher''' (Range is counted from the West starting point even if you started from the East)
**If you are trying to rank up aircraft with lower range, you may be required to bring a {{EquipmentLink|Type 2 Large Flying Boat}} (3+ Range) or {{EquipmentLink|PBY-5A Catalina}} (2+ Range) to increase your Land-base's range. 
**Due to the maximum range increase being 3+, you will be unable to use this method to rank up any aircrafts with 4 or lower range even if you bring a Large Flying Boat or PBY-51 Catalina. 
*Sortie 1 Submarine with a variety of aircraft to rank up in your Land-Base. You will start from East.
*Send your Land-Base Aircraft Support to attack node M only twice. 
*This will result in a Rank D loss, but your aircraft will be ranked up from Blank to Double Chevron after around 12 runs.
**If you send 1 aircraft with Anti-Submarine Patrol capabilities, like {{EquipmentLink|Prototype Toukai}} , you can avoid the loss.
*You may ignore morale on both your submarine and aircraft all the way.
*1 or 2 aircraft may be shot down sometimes which will only cost around 3 fuel to 5 bauxite per plane.

